3202
03:07:36.555 --> 03:07:38.055
We serve in East Christchurch.

3203
03:07:39.255 --> 03:07:42.355
Our club was founded in 1980 by a group of passionate locals

3204
03:07:42.355 --> 03:07:45.155
who wanted to give young people a safe, exciting place

3205
03:07:45.155 --> 03:07:47.635
to ride bikes, build skills, and grow.

3206
03:07:48.225 --> 03:07:49.635
Over the past 45 years,

3207
03:07:49.685 --> 03:07:51.395
we've become a cornerstone of our community.

3208
03:07:51.975 --> 03:07:53.435
Not just a sporting organization,

3209
03:07:53.935 --> 03:07:56.475
but a hub for connection, resilience, and pride.

3210
03:07:57.685 --> 03:07:59.155
After the Canterbury Earthquakes,

3211
03:07:59.495 --> 03:08:01.315
our community was deeply affected.

3212
03:08:01.775 --> 03:08:04.715
Infrastructure was damaged, families were displaced,

3213
03:08:04.775 --> 03:08:07.115
and antisocial behavior began to take root.

3214
03:08:07.895 --> 03:08:09.675
But through contestable community funding,

3215
03:08:09.835 --> 03:08:13.435
particularly from gaming machine proceeds, we rebuilt

3216
03:08:13.615 --> 03:08:15.715
and we didn't just restore what we lost,

3217
03:08:16.015 --> 03:08:17.955
we created something ordinary.

3218
03:08:19.305 --> 03:08:22.275
Over the past decade, our club has received approximately

3219
03:08:22.335 --> 03:08:26.195
$1.3 million in community grants, which have enabled us

3220
03:08:26.195 --> 03:08:29.035
to build and maintain two world class facilities in Bexley

3221
03:08:29.035 --> 03:08:31.235
Reserve, our BMX racing Track,

3222
03:08:31.365 --> 03:08:33.355
which was hosted regional national events

3223
03:08:33.815 --> 03:08:38.075
and will proudly hosted 2027 UCI Oceanic BMS Racing

3224
03:08:38.075 --> 03:08:41.355
Championships, a testament to its international standard

3225
03:08:42.255 --> 03:08:44.875
and the Nigel Mann Memorial Pump Track,

3226
03:08:45.165 --> 03:08:48.435
which hosted a UCI World Pump Track qualifier

3227
03:08:48.435 --> 03:08:51.115
and has received national recognition, including Merit

3228
03:08:51.175 --> 03:08:55.075
for Standing Project Recreation Ontario Rail Awards, uh,

3229
03:08:55.175 --> 03:08:56.595
in November, 2023,

3230
03:08:57.415 --> 03:09:00.995
and also winning the Beyond the Brief Placemaking RARA Award

3231
03:09:00.995 --> 03:09:02.235
